# seodit Matchers

seodit is a Playwright extension with SEO matchers. Each matcher is a plain `expect.extend` function.

Reference implementation: `packages/seodit/src/matchers/to-have-canonical.ts`.

## Layout

Flat files under `packages/seodit/src/matchers/` — only matcher files + `AGENTS.md`:

```text
matchers/
  AGENTS.md
  to-have-canonical.ts
  to-have-html-lang.ts
  to-have-jsonld.ts
```

No `index.ts`, `discover.ts`, or other infrastructure in this folder. Docs discovery lives in `apps/docs/lib/discover-matchers.ts`.

- File: `to-have-canonical.ts`
- Export: `toHaveCanonical`
- Docs slug: `to-have-canonical`

## Matcher body format

```typescript
import type { Page } from "@playwright/test";

/**
 * …TSDoc…
 */
export async function toHaveCanonical(page: Page, expected: string | RegExp) {
  const selector = 'link[rel="canonical"]';
  const actual = await page.locator(selector).getAttribute("href");
  const pass = typeof expected === "string" ? actual === expected : !!actual && expected.test(actual);

  return {
    pass,
    message: () => `Expected canonical: ${expected}\nReceived: ${actual}`,
  };
}
```

Rules:

- Plain `export async function toHave…(page, expected)` — no factories, no wrappers, no `create*Matcher`.
- Read via Playwright locator (`page.locator(...).getAttribute(...)`). Use `page.content()` only when locators are not enough (JSON-LD parse, etc.).
- Return `{ pass, message }` yourself. Do not wrap `baseExpect(...).toHaveAttribute` in try/catch.
- Keep the selector inside the function — do not export selector constants.
- No shared comparison helpers (`matchesExpected`, `ExpectedValue`) for simple attribute checks — compare inline (`===` / `RegExp.test`).
- Do not copy Playwright internals (`expectTypes`, `_expect`, `toMatchText`, `formatMatcherMessage`).
- Positive path only is fine; Playwright inverts `.not` from `pass`.

## TSDoc (docs source of truth)

1. One-line title before the first heading.
2. Short summary paragraph.
3. `## Why is this important?`
4. `## How to use this matcher?` — show `await expect(page).toHave…(...)` from `@/test/seodit`.
5. `## Further reading` — optional.

Docs MDX is generated by `apps/docs/scripts/generate-matcher-docs.mts`. Do not hand-edit generated pages except `content/docs/matchers/index.mdx`.

## Adding a matcher

1. Add `matchers/to-have-*.ts` in the format above.
2. Register in `playwright/index.ts` (`seoditMatchers` + `Matchers` types).
3. Re-export from `src/index.ts` if the package root should expose it.
4. Run docs generate / build.
